    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Select the correct statement(s) regarding CMOS implementation of NOT gates.</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "Noise Margin High (NM<sub>H</sub>) is always equal to the Noise Margin Low (NM<sub>L</sub>), irrespective of the sizing of transistors."
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "Dynamic power consumption during switching is zero."
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "For a logical high input under steady state, the nMOSFET is in the linear regime of operation."
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "Mobility of electrons never influences the switching speed of the NOT gate."
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "C"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>(a) NM<sub>L</sub> = V<sub>IL</sub> $$-$$ V<sub>OL</sub></p>\n<p>NM<sub>H</sub> = V<sub>OH</sub> $$-$$ V<sub>IH</sub></p>\n<p>when, V<sub>TN</sub> = | V<sub>TP</sub> |</p>\n<p>and K<sub>n</sub> = K<sub>p</sub></p>\n<p>V<sub>IT</sub> = $${{{V_{DD}}} \\over 2}$$ and NM<sub>L</sub> = NM<sub>H</sub></p>\n<p>when $$ \\uparrow {{{K_p}} \\over {{K_n}}}$$ > 1, V<sub>IL</sub> $$\\uparrow$$, V<sub>IH</sub> $$\\uparrow$$</p>\n<p>NM<sub>H</sub> $$\\downarrow$$ and NM<sub>L</sub> $$\\uparrow$$</p>\n<p>When, $$ \\downarrow {{{K_p}} \\over {{K_n}}}$$ < 1, V<sub>IL</sub> $$\\downarrow$$, V<sub>IH</sub> $$\\uparrow$$</p>\n<p>NM<sub>H</sub> $$\\uparrow$$ and NM<sub>L</sub> $$\\uparrow$$</p>\n<p>i.e. NM<sub>L</sub> and NM<sub>H</sub> depends on transistor sizing and they are equal for certain condition only.</p>\n<p>(b) Dynamic power consumption during switching is non-zero due to capacitive loading of next state.</p>\n<p>(c) For $$\\matrix{\n   {\\mathop {{V_{DD}} - \\left| {{V_{TP}}} \\right| \\le {V_{in}} \\le {V_{DD}}}\\limits_{(logic\\,high\\,input)}  \\Rightarrow } & {PMOS \\to Cut - off}  \\cr \n   {} & {NMOS \\to \\,Linear}  \\cr \n\n } $$</p>\n<p>(d) Switching speed depends on charging and discharging of load capacitor for pull up and pull down of output voltage respectively.</p>\n<p>Fast charging and discharging of capacitor depends on mobility of charge carrier.</p>\n<p>$$\\tau$$<sub>charging</sub> = R<sub>PMOS</sub> C<sub>L</sub> (to bring o/p at logic high)</p>\n<p>$$\\tau$$<sub>discharging</sub> = R<sub>NMOS</sub> C<sub>L</sub> (to bring o/p at logic low)</p>\n<p>and also propagation delay,</p>\n<p>$${\\tau _p} = {{{\\tau _{PLH}} + {\\tau _{PHL}}} \\over 2}$$</p>\n<p>where, $${T_{PLH}} = {{{C_L}\\,{V_{DD}}} \\over {{\\mu _p}{C_{ox}}\\left( {{W \\over L}} \\right){{({V_{GS}} - {V_{Tp}})}^2}}}$$</p>\n<p>$${T_{PHL}} = {{{C_L}\\,{V_{DD}}} \\over {{\\mu _p}{C_{ox}}\\left( {{W \\over L}} \\right){{({V_{GS}} - {V_{TN}})}^2}}}$$</p>\n<p>Using average charge model.</p>\n<p>Hence, (c) is only correct statement.</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2022,
    "yearKey": "gate-ece-2022",
